            "body": "> I guess such popups could temporarily unset 'title', then restore it on WinLeave. nvim_open_win() also has a style=minimal option, maybe this could fit there (though it seems to target window-local options mostly).\r\n\r\nThe options is not restored.\r\n\r\n```\r\nvim.opt.title = true\r\nvim.opt.titlestring = \"%F %r\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe title is changed when window move.\r\n`nvim-cmp` seems move windows to update the popup window.\r\nSo it flickers.",
