            "body": "Proposal from https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/22457#issuecomment-1448655680 :\r\n\r\n> Often float popups are also used for more long lived things, like terminal sessions. Also, a split window can also be a temporary input window. If we add a feature to disable title setting, it should be (both ways) independent of `w_floating` .\r\n\r\n",
